\subsubsection{Maintaining biodiversity: From here to eternity?$<$/h3$>$ 

There has been substantial recent progress in determining the distributions and identity of vulnerable species, and in understanding how (and where) human activity is leading to extinctions. Pimm \emph{et al.} review the current state of knowledge and ask what the future rates of species extinction will be, how well protected areas will slow extinction rates, and how the remaining gaps in knowledge might be filled.$<$/p$>$

